{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"079debef-f50e-4a40-986a-9ee3b6c68f44","content":"It's a simple change. In your project file, either **remove** the `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` property or set it to `false`:\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <!-- Remove or set to false: -->\n    <!-- <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest> -->\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n```\n\n**What this does:**\n- `MSTest.Sdk` defaults to **Microsoft.Testing.Platform** already. The `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` property was opting you *back* into the legacy VSTest runner.\n- Removing it gives you the new platform runner out of the box.\n\n**Key differences to be aware of:**\n1. **CLI changes** — Use `dotnet test` as before, but the underlying runner is different. You can also run the test executable directly.\n2. **`.runsettings`** — Most settings carry over, but review for any VSTest-specific extensions.\n3. **Test output** — Console output format changes slightly.\n4. **Third-party adapters** — If you use VSTest-specific adapters (e.g., custom loggers/collectors), verify they have Microsoft.Testing.Platform equivalents.\n\nAfter making the change, run `dotnet test` to verify everything passes.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"631fce69-0fbf-4d30-b7e0-0122ee01d79c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The repository doesn't seem to have specific documentation about this migration. Let me answer based on my knowledge of MSTest.Sdk and the Microsoft.Testing.Platform migration.","outputTokens":373,"requestId":"4817:99ACC:31E8025:3679E33:69FBE2C4"},"id":"88602bb1-718b-4bca-8bf6-9425111f58b0","timestamp":"2026-05-07T00:54:40.274Z","parentId":"09dedc3e-2aa0-404f-8993-8bdbed4a98bf"}
